# Tests Required

**Every code change that affects behavior MUST include or update tests.** Use `test-driven-development` skill for new features.

## Backend — PHPUnit

Framework: **PHPUnit** (`php artisan test`). Skill: `laravel-testing`.

| Change | Test location |
|--------|----------------|
| API endpoint | `backend/tests/Feature/Api/` |
| Admin endpoint | `backend/tests/Feature/Admin/` |
| Repository / scope | `backend/tests/Unit/` or Feature |
| Form Request rules | Feature test asserting 422 |

```php
// Feature test pattern
public function test_guest_can_list_published_news(): void
{
    News::factory()->published()->count(3)->create();

    $this->getJson('/api/v1/news')
        ->assertOk()
        ->assertJsonCount(3, 'data');
}
```

- Use `RefreshDatabase` for DB tests.
- `Sanctum::actingAs($admin)` for admin routes.
- Fake: `Mail::fake()`, `Queue::fake()`, `Storage::fake()`.

```bash
make test-backend
# or: docker compose exec backend php artisan test
```

## Frontend — Vitest + Testing Library

Framework: **Vitest** + **@testing-library/react**. Skills: `vitest`, `frontend-testing`.

| Change | Test location |
|--------|----------------|
| Component | `frontend/src/**/*.test.tsx` (colocated) |
| Zod schema | `frontend/src/schemas/*.test.ts` |
| Hook | `frontend/src/hooks/*.test.ts` |

```typescript
import { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react';
import { describe, it, expect } from 'vitest';

describe('NewsCard', () => {
  it('renders title', () => {
    render(<NewsCard title="Berita" slug="berita" />);
    expect(screen.getByText('Berita')).toBeInTheDocument();
  });
});
```

```bash
make test-frontend
# or: docker compose exec frontend npm test
```

## Definition of done

- [ ] New/changed behavior has a test
- [ ] `make test-backend` passes (if backend touched)
- [ ] `make test-frontend` passes (if frontend touched)
- [ ] `verification-before-completion` — show test output before claiming done

## Exceptions (no test required)

- `.mdc` rules, docs-only, `package-lock.json` from install — still run tests if CI would.
